Defendant Lisa Yvonne Edgeston in court with attorney Sarah Zwach.  Defendant Lisa Yvonne Edgeston in custody.  Jennifer Jean Tate appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.  Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm. Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.
